<subSubSection id="C338D6252385C03D8A5CE313B7239277" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4C7D4BA74AB60505D648E6DB5A285D9B" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BF490D452F0180AB002BFB7381CC0279" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Basidiomata distinctly small. A pileus a bit slimy when moist. Stipe light yellow, base turning to light brown with age. Cheilocystidia common in clavate with rounded apex, rarely fusiform. Pileipellis occasionally with coarse excrescences.</paragraph>
