(collection no. MY0259); Fujian Province, Nanping City, Wuyi Mountain, 
<date id="006E5D46FAADA1F8AF51229C9210000E" value="2020-07-25">25 Jul 2020</date>
, Qin Na, Yupeng Ge, Yaping Hu, Hui Zeng, and Zewei Liu, 
<emphasis id="B8B970257E9E2E2FBEC9FBF28A94AE27" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">FFAAS0375</emphasis>
(collection no. MY0544); Zhejiang Province, Hangzhou City, Tianmu Mountain, 
<date id="906BE04992CEDFB8C6AC80645D113FB0" value="2021-07-30">30 Jul 2021</date>
, Qin Na, Yupeng Ge, Zewei Liu, and Yulan Sun, 
<emphasis id="A597B789904D9C5A88CC248C9728F607" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">FFAAS0371</emphasis>
(collection no. MY0424); Lishui City, Liandu District, Baiyun National Forest Park, 
<date id="3CDE0E02A759BFBBE73607DC3D7DE495" value="2021-08-02">2 Aug 2021</date>
, Qin Na, Yupeng Ge, Zewei Liu, and Yulan Sun, 
<emphasis id="84872E1CF8DBC484767DEC105967C323" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">FFAAS0372</emphasis>
(collection no. MY0478), Qingtian County, Shigu Lake, 
<date id="EC9C64C49B64EACCCAEE7C8F5DC87951" value="2021-08-06">6 Aug 2021</date>
, Qin Na, Yupeng Ge, Junqing Yan, Zewei Liu, and Yulan Sun, 
<emphasis id="B66B526B4FB4E431C733EF68809C5EA0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">FFAAS0374</emphasis>
(collection no. MY0527).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C1BB6CE63A3CB5A4B413B14428142DA7" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="F68ED7D3D1302F7D25951C992941D948" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DE7289C16BBD2515EF4331BFB5EFACEA" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">
Characteristics such as tiny omphalinoid basidiomata, decurrent lamellae, inamyloid and narrowly ellipsoid to cylindrical basidiospores, sarcodimitic tramal tissues, a pileipellis with pigmented terminal elements, and long cylindrical or clavate caulocystidia support the placement of this species in 
<taxonomicName id="42153ADB7AFCF98FF374E7FAED4BDDB1" authorityName="Singer" authorityYear="1951" class="Basidiomycetes" family="Porotheleaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gerronema" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="82F2F7A8C17FCCA419C2F9EFBDD8281E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Gerronema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A2DB1EE73BFF23DE61C47E97A36CE20C" author="Singer, R" journalOrPublisher="Flora Neotropica" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 84" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4393664" refId="B56" refString="Singer, R, 1970. Omphalinae (Clitocybeae - Tricholomataceae, Basidiomycetes). Flora Neotropica 3: 1 - 84, http://www.jstor.org/stable/4393664" title="Omphalinae (Clitocybeae - Tricholomataceae, Basidiomycetes)." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4393664" volume="3" year="1970">Singer 1970</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="34BD55E8DE6DD18E377D2EDA81711DE4" author="Singer, R" journalOrPublisher="Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" refId="B58" refString="Singer, R, 1986. The Agaricales in modern taxonomy, 4th edn. Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein" title="The Agaricales in modern taxonomy, 4 th edn." year="1986">1986</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="FECA83CFC41792060AD762B17FE5A6A0" author="Norvell, L" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="379 - 407" refId="B44" refString="Norvell, L, Redhead, S, Ammirati, J, 1994. Omphalina sensu lato in North America 1-2. 1: Omphalina wynniae and the genus Chrysomphalina. 2: Omphalina sensu Bigelow. Mycotaxon 50: 379 - 407" title="Omphalina sensu lato in North America 1 - 2. 1: Omphalina wynniae and the genus Chrysomphalina. 2: Omphalina sensu Bigelow." volume="50" year="1994">Norvell et al. 1994</bibRefCitation>
). Because of its small basidiomata, decurrent lamellae, and subregular pileus trama, 
<taxonomicName id="214799B38EF18BD09969D1A7AC4F5285" genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. kuruvense" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="kuruvense">
<emphasis id="CEF3D716ABB0208CDE1435062801E2E1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. kuruvense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is difficult to distinguish from 
<taxonomicName id="6B1512E308AB3689914371C606B5923C" genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. microcarpum" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="microcarpum">
<emphasis id="4EC2C904628203EF686C20F02170059F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. microcarpum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but its pileus is orange yellow all over, no cheilocystidia or pleurocystidia are present, and its pileocystidia and caulocystidia are somewhat thick-walled (
<bibRefCitation id="78C9AFEFAB09049C1C5457D187906257" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.364.1.5" author="Latha, KPD" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="081 - 091" refId="B30" refString="Latha, KPD, Nanu, S, Sharafudheen, SA, Manimohan, P, 2018. Two new species of Gerronema (Agaricales, Basidiomycota) from Kerala State, India. Phytotaxa 364 (1): 081 - 091, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.364.1.5" title="Two new species of Gerronema (Agaricales, Basidiomycota) from Kerala State, India." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.364.1.5" volume="364" year="2018">Latha et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="708C2FE288A0CEFEDF812C05A3210AC6" class="Basidiomycetes" family="Porotheleaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gerronema nemorale" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="nemorale">
<emphasis id="2D6D47DCA4496C70BB205C396ECFE0BB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Gerronema nemorale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has certain morphological similarities to 
<taxonomicName id="E33671726EADCABBAD2C4DCECD1AD958" genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. microcarpum" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="microcarpum">
<emphasis id="6C369FACD52F59C9379A505DDA4195EB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. microcarpum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, namely, the presence of tiny yellowish basidiomata, decurrent lamellae, and cylindrical basidiospores (
<bibRefCitation id="9E047D1E715018D77F2CF853848273CE" DOI="https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.60204" author="Antonin, V" journalOrPublisher="Czech Mycology" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="197 - 212" refId="B1" refString="Antonin, V, Ryoo, R, Shin, HD, 2008. Gerronema nemorale (Basidiomycota, Agaricomycetes): Anatomic-morphological, cultivational, enzymatic and molecular characteristics and its first records in the Republic of Korea. Czech Mycology 60 (2): 197 - 212, DOI: https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.60204" title="Gerronema nemorale (Basidiomycota, Agaricomycetes): Anatomic-morphological, cultivational, enzymatic and molecular characteristics and its first records in the Republic of Korea." url="https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.60204" volume="60" year="2008">
<normalizedToken id="894BF768A64EB88BC61F038EED1D423B" originalValue="Antonín">Antonin</normalizedToken>
et al. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="9F3684C85469C0B8EC356F14B7D3F0BD" DOI="https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.63101" author="Antonin, V" journalOrPublisher="Czech Mycology" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 11" refId="B2" refString="Antonin, V, Beran, M, Borovicka, J, Dvorak, D, Holec, J, 2011. Clitocybula familia (Fungi, Agaricales) - taxonomy, distribution, ecology and first records in the Czech Republic and Slovakia. Czech Mycology 63 (1): 1 - 11, DOI: https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.63101" title="Clitocybula familia (Fungi, Agaricales) - taxonomy, distribution, ecology and first records in the Czech Republic and Slovakia." url="https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.63101" volume="63" year="2011">2011</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="6B8BFC86D2F1A7F2B1F47CF5388EECFB" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1744-697X.2009.00170.x" author="Takashi, O" journalOrPublisher="Japanese Society of Grassland Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="31 - 36" refId="B61" refString="Takashi, O, 2009. Decomposition of grass leaves by ligninolytic litter-decomposing fungi. Japanese Society of Grassland Science 56: 31 - 36, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1744-697X.2009.00170.x" title="Decomposition of grass leaves by ligninolytic litter-decomposing fungi." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1744-697X.2009.00170.x" volume="56" year="2009">Takashi 2009</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName id="A9105DBCE468D0F0FC41AEAAD4425D37" genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. nemorale" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="nemorale">
<emphasis id="B19EDE62429848CBA8D2620FB7F4AB31" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. nemorale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having a pileus with an olive tint, a longer stipe with conspicuous white mycelioid bristles, and larger terminal elements of the pileipellis (up to 150 
<normalizedToken id="5C2CE0C8FC343B70BE32B75BEF999CD5" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="9FC2A21C296081E486BA55A83936F389" DOI="https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.60204" author="Antonin, V" journalOrPublisher="Czech Mycology" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="197 - 212" refId="B1" refString="Antonin, V, Ryoo, R, Shin, HD, 2008. Gerronema nemorale (Basidiomycota, Agaricomycetes): Anatomic-morphological, cultivational, enzymatic and molecular characteristics and its first records in the Republic of Korea. Czech Mycology 60 (2): 197 - 212, DOI: https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.60204" title="Gerronema nemorale (Basidiomycota, Agaricomycetes): Anatomic-morphological, cultivational, enzymatic and molecular characteristics and its first records in the Republic of Korea." url="https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.60204" volume="60" year="2008">
<normalizedToken id="979B7183A70C1703F07FE8513C477F54" originalValue="Antonín">Antonin</normalizedToken>
et al. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="412345DB2C446A991648610799CAF187" DOI="https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.63101" author="Antonin, V" journalOrPublisher="Czech Mycology" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 11" refId="B2" refString="Antonin, V, Beran, M, Borovicka, J, Dvorak, D, Holec, J, 2011. Clitocybula familia (Fungi, Agaricales) - taxonomy, distribution, ecology and first records in the Czech Republic and Slovakia. Czech Mycology 63 (1): 1 - 11, DOI: https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.63101" title="Clitocybula familia (Fungi, Agaricales) - taxonomy, distribution, ecology and first records in the Czech Republic and Slovakia." url="https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.63101" volume="63" year="2011">2011</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="AD39C5C9FA395162EE7A3EE5796983B6" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1744-697X.2009.00170.x" author="Takashi, O" journalOrPublisher="Japanese Society of Grassland Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="31 - 36" refId="B61" refString="Takashi, O, 2009. Decomposition of grass leaves by ligninolytic litter-decomposing fungi. Japanese Society of Grassland Science 56: 31 - 36, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1744-697X.2009.00170.x" title="Decomposition of grass leaves by ligninolytic litter-decomposing fungi." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1744-697X.2009.00170.x" volume="56" year="2009">Takashi 2009</bibRefCitation>
). Compared with 
<taxonomicName id="3D79F11FCA4E3CBDC64A37A3F4503B44" genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. microcarpum" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="microcarpum">
<emphasis id="CB8474F87FF7A5C0EEB07497F66D686D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. microcarpum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D6CF6A27CA8ADBE69FEC91A2E35210A7" genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. subchrysophyllum" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="subchrysophyllum">
<emphasis id="1115148D029F55C5170EC9860FF9E262" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. subchrysophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Murrill) Singer has an olive-umber pileus fading to grayish when old, larger and ellipsoid basidiospores (4.3-8.5 
<normalizedToken id="11A9740AA86B03E4EEDAFD081D0D54B6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-6.3 
<normalizedToken id="8E64728F13ADD12F6E741DAF8AB6CFEC" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
), and sometimes basidiole-like cheilocystidia (
<bibRefCitation id="57D4CF897E33A9BF17B1ECC9CFFA5066" author="Singer, R" journalOrPublisher="Flora Neotropica" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 84" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4393664" refId="B56" refString="Singer, R, 1970. Omphalinae (Clitocybeae - Tricholomataceae, Basidiomycetes). Flora Neotropica 3: 1 - 84, http://www.jstor.org/stable/4393664" title="Omphalinae (Clitocybeae - Tricholomataceae, Basidiomycetes)." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4393664" volume="3" year="1970">Singer 1970</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="B9E4856F26B2FA1534150B0BD9E8C817" class="Basidiomycetes" family="Porotheleaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gerronema keralense" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="keralense">
<emphasis id="88E609E2E06623AD9328F63ACD5FA88F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Gerronema keralense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="AB8FDC4789C87E74CBFBC907D8C25F26" genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. strombodes" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="strombodes">
<emphasis id="DFA43BB5756500FBED75145AC6C8F8E5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. strombodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are easily mistaken for 
<taxonomicName id="16EB09A4B8851E5042ABB0DF6C2DB2A2" genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. microcarpum" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="microcarpum">
